parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the occupant restraint control can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbags may not deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: the airbag warning light flashes on and off
the headrest deploys without a crash
the seat belts do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy in a crash
the seat belts do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headrest deployment can cause the headrest to deploy without a crash, which can cause injury or distraction to the driver or passenger.
symptoms: The headrest deploys without a crash
the headrest does not reset after deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of power
the dashboard gauges flash on and off
the radio and other electrical components malfunction
and the vehicle may shut off while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body control can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of power
the throttle body control light illuminates
and the vehicle may not accelerate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbag may not deploy properly in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: and the horn may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the vehicle to lose heat, which can be a safety issue in cold weather conditions.
symptoms: and the heater core may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of power
and the transmission may slip or hesitate to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, which can lead to engine damage, loss of power, and accidents.

symptoms: oil filter housing cracking or chipping

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle body/Tipm failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and accidents.
